<span id="freeTextContainer114194950574844958">This is officially the most boring book I&apos;ve read this year.<br/><br/>There were some interesting moments but they were too few to compensate. <br/>You&apos;ll learn more about random rainforest frogs than you ever wanted...<br/><br/>Also I find that while reading some non fiction you have to like the author to a certain extent and I just couldn&apos;t here. One moment during the book she writes about how she tried to visit a certain location and asked the lady working at the gift shop to give her a tour. The employee obviously t</span>
  <span id="freeText114194950574844958" style="display:none">This is officially the most boring book I've read this year.<br /><br />There were some interesting moments but they were too few to compensate. <br />You'll learn more about random rainforest frogs than you ever wanted...<br /><br />Also I find that while reading some non fiction you have to like the author to a certain extent and I just couldn't here. One moment during the book she writes about how she tried to visit a certain location and asked the lady working at the gift shop to give her a tour. The employee obviously told her she was busy and I couldn't help but resent the author for being salty about it as she wrote that "as far as she could tell they were the only ones there". Like come on.<br /><br />Don't recommend.</span>
