        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1562091007" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8434629110765844833">Most depressing book that I&apos;ve ever read. The physical science of man&apos;s injury to Earth began since he emerged as a species, and now is at its zenith. In spite of the evidence, not much is being done to reduce the damage. I felt sicker and sicker as I read on, and I hated picking the book up once I&apos;d put it down. As a species, humanity is self-serving and aggressive. I&apos;ve watched Trump pooh-pooh climate change, knowing that our oceans are becoming acidic which is going to kill off microscope mar</span>
  <span id="freeText8434629110765844833" style="display:none">Most depressing book that I've ever read. The physical science of man's injury to Earth began since he emerged as a species, and now is at its zenith. In spite of the evidence, not much is being done to reduce the damage. I felt sicker and sicker as I read on, and I hated picking the book up once I'd put it down. As a species, humanity is self-serving and aggressive. I've watched Trump pooh-pooh climate change, knowing that our oceans are becoming acidic which is going to kill off microscope marine food for salmon, whales etc., kill reefs - which has nothing to do with temperature and everything to do with CO2 levels. Who will the last survivors be? Like everything related to extinction, will they look at each other and say, "Oh, I guess we should have paid attention sooner."? <br /><br />Read it and weep. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8434629110765844833" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

