      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/45840.Elizabeth_Kolbert">About Elizabeth Kolbert</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/45840.Elizabeth_Kolbert"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1380812913p3/45840.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/45840.Elizabeth_Kolbert">Elizabeth Kolbert
</a></div>
<div class='goodreadsAuthorBadge'></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
1,665
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6857197644793539177"><strong>Elizabeth Kolbert</strong> is a staff writer at <em>The New Yorker</em>. She is the author of <em>Field Notes from a Catastrophe: Man, Nature, and Climate Change</em> and <em>The Sixth Extinction: An Unnatural History</em>. She lives in Williamstown, Massachusetts, with her husband and children.</span>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

